				\begin{document}$$ DMI={\beta}_0+{\beta}_1\;ADG+{\beta}_2\;MB{W}^{0.75}+{\varepsilon}_1 $$\end{document}DMI=β0+β1ADG+β2MBW0.75+ε1

Where β0 is the intercept, β1 and β2 are the regression coefficients of the variables ADG and MBW0.75, respectively, and ε1 is the residue of the equation (i.e. RFI). RWG was calculated as the residue of the regression equation to predict ADG based on DMI and MBW:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
